<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Terms and Conditions</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        .container {
            background: #ffffff;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            padding: 30px;
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: #007bff;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .list-group-item {
            font-size: 1rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
            border: none;
            padding: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
        .list-group-item:nth-child(odd) {
            background-color: #e9ecef;
        }
        .list-group {
            border: none;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container my-5">
        <h1 class="text-center">Terms and Conditions</h1>
        <ul class="list-group">
            <li class="list-group-item">Fuel: The lessee is responsible for the cost of fuel.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Unlimited Km: If the client specifies a particular state as their travel destination, they can drive an unlimited number of kilometres within that state.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Change in Travel Destination: If the lessee changes their travel destination and moves outside the selected state limits, the rental company will apply destination-specific rates for the new location. This means that the client will be charged additional fees or adjusted rates based on the new state or destination they travel to.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Booking Cancellation: If a booking is cancelled 24 hours before the scheduled time, cancellation charges will apply.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Garage Downtime: If the vehicle is involved in an accident, the lessee is responsible for the downtime charges.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Insurance: Insurance is available for damages above ₹1,00,000 for cars below ₹10 lakhs and above ₹1,50,000 for cars above ₹10 lakhs.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Minimum Booking: The minimum booking duration is 12 hours.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">E-Aadhar and License Verification: E-Aadhar and driving licenses are verified before rental.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Damage Charges: Major damage is the lessee's responsibility; minor damage (e.g., dents, scratches) will be charged immediately.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Tyre Damage: The lessee is responsible for tyre damage due to punctures or cuts.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Speeding and Insurance: Insurance is void if the vehicle is driven over 100 km/h.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Refundable Deposit: A refundable deposit is required for all cars. It may be forfeited in the case of damage or an accident.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Missing Accessories: Lessees are charged for missing or lost accessories and tools.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Lessee Responsibility: The lessee is responsible for daily upkeep, police fines, taxes, and maintenance.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Rate Changes: Rates are subject to change without prior notice.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Day Definition: A rental day is considered 24 hours. An extra hour incurs a charge of ₹200.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Speeding Fine: A fine of up to ₹2000 will apply for each instance of exceeding the speed limit by more than 100 km/h.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">No Alcohol or Smoking: Alcohol consumption and smoking are prohibited in the car, with a ₹1000 fine for non-compliance.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Unauthorized Repairs: Vehicle repairs or damages outside the authorized service are prohibited and may lead to additional charges.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Immediate Intimation: Any damage or accidents must be reported immediately.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Theft and Non-payment: Misuse, theft, or non-payment will be reported to the nearest police station.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Deposit Return: The security deposit will be returned within 24-48 hours after the rental.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Accident Impact: In case of an accident, the vehicle's resale value may decrease, and the lessee will need to pay the difference.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Payment Method: Only online payments are accepted.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
